Lens database
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The bundled lens-correction database (data/lens-profiles.json and the copy in
dist/data/) is derived from the Lensfun project's lens database:

    https://lensfun.github.io/
    https://github.com/lensfun/lensfun

The Lensfun lens database is distributed under the Creative Commons
Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported license (CC BY-SA 3.0):

    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/

The JSON file shipped here is a format conversion of that database (camera and
lens calibration coefficients for distortion, transverse chromatic aberration,
and vignetting). It remains licensed under CC BY-SA 3.0; this NOTICE preserves
the required attribution and share-alike terms. Modifications to the calibration
data, if any, are likewise available under CC BY-SA 3.0.

The MIT license of this extension's source code does NOT relicense the lens
database; the database keeps its CC BY-SA 3.0 terms.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Adobe Lens Profile (.lcp) import
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This extension can read Adobe Lens Profile (.lcp) files supplied by the user.
"Adobe" and "Lightroom" are trademarks of Adobe Inc. This project is not
affiliated with or endorsed by Adobe. No Adobe lens profiles are redistributed
with this extension; users import their own.
